      "text": "Cheryl celebrates 15 ‚Äòamazing‚Äô years in the music industry Cheryl (Yui Mok/PA) \n  \nCheryl has thanked fans for their support as she celebrates 15 years in the music industry. \nThe singer, 34, tweeted a series of messages saying she has experienced ‚Äúthe great the good the bad and the ugly‚Äù since she found fame in Girls Aloud in 2002, but that she would not change her experience. \nIt just dawned on me that next month I will have been in this industry for 15 years üò¶!! ‚Ä¶ \n‚Äî Cheryl (@CherylOfficial) October 23, 2017 \nShe said: ‚ÄúIt just dawned on me that next month I will have been in this industry for 15 years !! \n‚ÄúI‚Äôve experienced the great the good the bad and the ugly! And I‚Äôm happy for it all.. I wouldn‚Äôt change a bit of it ! \n‚ÄúThank you to all of you who have been by my side .. and watched me grow and learn and have been growing and learning with me .. so amazing.‚Äù \nThe star ended her post with a heart emoji. \nCheryl won a place in Girls Aloud on reality television show Popstars: The Rivals. \nGirls Aloud were formed in 2002 (Ian West/PA) \nShe went on to have a solo chart career after the group split and was also a judge on X Factor. \nThe star became a mother this year when she and boyfriend Liam Payne welcomed their son Bear.",
