      "title": "Geri Horner ‚Äònot helpful‚Äô when she appeared on my show ‚Äì Ken Bruce",
      "country": "GB",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T02:12:52Z",
      "url": "http://www.dudleynews.co.uk/leisure/showbiz/15614729.Geri_Horner____not_helpful____when_she_appeared_on_my_show_____Ken_Bruce/",
      "host": "dudleynews.co.uk",
      "text": "Geri Horner ‚Äònot helpful‚Äô when she appeared on my show ‚Äì Ken Bruce Geri Horner was ‚Äònot helpful‚Äô when she appeared on my show ‚Äì Ken Bruce (Lorenzo Agius/BBC) \n  \nKen Bruce has said that one of his most memorable moments on his BBC Radio 2 show involved Geri Horner and her flatulent dog. \nThe radio presenter has also revealed that he thinks his ‚Äúnormal life‚Äù approach to presenting is the reason he appeals to his loyal audience. \nThe 66-year-old told the Radio Times of one of his career lowlights, in which ‚Äúa member of a girl group ‚Äì well, it‚Äôs Geri Halliwell ‚Äì who was not helpful, shall we say‚Äù. \nGeri Horner (formerly Halliwell) (Ian West/PA) \nBruce said: ‚ÄúShe brought in somebody she had met on the street, and this was just after a major terrorism incident.‚Äù \nHe added: ‚ÄúAnd a dog that farted.‚Äù \nBruce has been a BBC fixture for more than three decades, is Radio 2‚Äôs longest-serving male broadcaster, and his mid-morning show has an audience of more than 8 million. \nBut of his secret to success, he said he believes there is none. \nHe said: ‚ÄúI just come on and am roughly myself ‚Äì or a slightly better version ‚Äì and hope that‚Äôs what people like. \n‚ÄúI don‚Äôt do laugh-out-loud stuff: wry smiles are what I like to get.‚Äù \nThe veteran DJ said: ‚ÄúWould something that works for someone my age work for someone of 15 who is listening in the car with their mum, or someone who is 35? \nBBC Radio 2‚Äôs Ken Bruce (Lorenzo Agius/BBC) \n‚ÄúBroadly speaking, I do normal life: things going wrong with your washing machine, children not cleaning their bedrooms. \n‚ÄúI don‚Äôt go to showbiz parties, but I wouldn‚Äôt talk about it if I did. If you talk about digging the garden ‚Äì not everyone‚Äôs got a garden. Not everyone can afford a car. \n‚ÄúYou have to not say things that‚Äôll make people think, ‚ÄòHe doesn‚Äôt begin to understand my life‚Äô.‚Äù \nRadio Times is on sale now.",
