      "host": "aol.co.uk",
      "text": "Curry fined $50,000 for throwing mouthpiece at official By Omnisport 23 Oct 2017, 23:31 - \nStephen Curry was fined $50,000 for throwing his mouthpiece in the direction of a game official during the final minute of Saturday's loss to the Memphis Grizzlies, the NBA announced. \nThe Golden State Warriors guard tossed his mouthpiece toward an official when no foul was called as he drove to the hoop for a layup. \nHe was immediately ejected but said after the game he was not trying to intentionally throw it at the official. \n\"I got better aim than that. I threw it out of frustration,\" he said. \nAs part of the same incident, Warriors forward Andre Iguodala was fined $15,000 for verbally abusing a game official. \nThe Warriors were called for three technical fouls on the night while there were a combined 54 fouls between the two teams. The Warriors were called for 28 of those fouls and 26 were called on the Grizzlies. \nCurry finished the night with 37 points on nine-of-17 shooting. Let us send you our Newsletter Our editors will email you a roundup of their favourite stories from across AOL Sign up using your AOL email or",
