      "host": "birminghammail.co.uk",
      "text": "What's On What are the Christmas bank holidays for 2017? It can be tricky to work out what time off is guaranteed over Christmas - but here's the answer Share Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Get What's On updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email \nFor many of us, Christmas means some guaranteed time off work and a chance to be at home with the family. \nOr maybe you choose to make a getaway from festive tradition and jet off in search of winter sun. \nWhatever your plans, they will depend on what public holidays can be taken into account. Read More \nThe more bank holidays you can include, the less of your holiday entitlement you need to use up. \nSo what are the Christmas bank holidays for 2017? What time off will you have this Christmas? (Image: Getty Images/iStockphoto) \nThis year, the public holidays for the festive season do not fall on a weekend. \nChristmas Day (December 25) is on a Monday, followed by Boxing Day (December 26) on the Tuesday. Read More",
