      "url": "https://sbnn.co.uk/2017/10/23/aabs-outsourcing-division-grows-25-2017/",
      "host": "sbnn.co.uk",
      "text": "AAB‚Äôs outsourcing division grows 25% in 2017   Anderson Anderson & Brown LLP (AAB), one of the leading independent firms of Chartered Accountants and Business Advisors in Scotland, has announced that fee income within its outsourcing division has grown by 25% in the last 12 months, driven by 50 new clients coming on board throughout the UK. This new business gained has resulted in 5 new posts being created in this division alone, as well as giving rise to 5 promotions within the team. Whilst over half of AAB‚Äôs outsourcing clients are still UK headquartered an increasing number of international businesses coming to the UK are now working in partnership with AAB, with many of these businesses being internationally owned or managed from overseas, in a host of countries including Norway, Italy, USA, UAE, Italy, Mexico, Australia and Russia. Through AAB‚Äôs cloud based outsourcing solutions, businesses can be transformed by a service which takes care of all accounting, bookkeeping, UK and international tax, VAT, global payroll, project management and data capture requirements. The growth achieved in this area has been as a result of both client and market demand for cloud-based services which offer businesses the opportunity to gain real-time information on their key business areas, from anywhere in the world, at any time. Steve Mitchell, Partner and Head of Outsourcing at AAB commented ‚ÄúTechnology truly has made the world a smaller place and because of cloud-based software systems, users can access real-time data from any location, globally, at any time, as long as they have access to the internet, meaning that they constantly have an up-to-date view of their business finances available at their fingertips. We are delighted with the significant growth in our outsourcing business in the last year and are now working with a fantastic range of clients across a broad range of sectors and geographical locations. We are very much focussed on working in partnership with our clients to deliver them the best outsourcing solution to add value to their business .‚Äù",
