      "host": "urbanvault.co.uk",
      "text": "23/10/2017 Team Salut debut their HOT PROPERTY music video featuring Tion Wayne, Afro B, and Eugy via GRM Daily Coming on the back of unveiling their debut single ‚Äò Hot Property ‚Äô a few weeks ago, to rave reviews and early support from BBC 1Xtra, Capital Xtra, Spotify, Rinse FM, Radar Radio, MTV UK, Highsnobiety, Earmilk and Link Up TV among others, London-based artist/producer trio Team Salut are excited to debut the brand new music video for their hot new track, featuring Tion Wayne, Afro B and Eugy. Premiered via GRM Daily, the video for ‚ÄòHot Property‚Äô sees Team Salut collaborating with burgeoning video director and filmmaker Ray Fiasco, who has previously worked with the likes of Tinie Tempah, Krept & Konan, Bonkaz and Shakka, to deliver a lively, energetic and eye-catching visual affair, which not only brings the already infectious record further to life, but also highlights Team Salut as true performing artists, with vibrant personalities and strong performance prowess. With their pioneering UK ‚ÄòAfroWave‚Äô sound continuing to break ground internationally, and ‚ÄòHeavy‚Äô, their recent production collaboration with Anne-Marie, poised to break into the UK Top 40, as well as another anticipated party for Boxpark on November 16, with Kenny Allstar, DJ P Montana, and special guest Afro B, Team Salut are having a impressive final few months of the year, and with ‚ÄòHot Property‚Äô continuing to spread like wildfire across the country, the London trio are fast becoming strong contenders for ones to watch in 2018. Speaking about the video for ‚ÄòHot Property‚Äô, Team Salut say, ‚ÄúThese are the hottest artists in the scene and we as Team Salut are bringing them together. Having put our stamp as producers on huge tracks like ‚ÄòDance For Me‚Äô, ‚ÄòMinor‚Äô and ‚ÄòStay Winning‚Äô, this is our video debut as outright artists. The video reflects the vibe of the music, but more than that ‚Äì the video reflects the vibe of all us guys together under one flag‚Äù.",
