      "text": "Kim Wilde announces first full UK theatre tour in 30 years Kim Wilde (Matt Crossick/PA) \nGet the latest local news straight to your inbox every day Sign up \nKim Wilde has announced her first full UK theatre tour in 30 years. \nThe singer will embark on a 19-date string of shows across England, Scotland and Wales next spring to coincide with the release of her 14th studio album Here Come The Aliens. \nThe record follows the British singer‚Äôs last release Wilde Winter Songbook in 2013 and Snapshots in 2011. \nKim Wilde in 1983 (PA) \nBest known for 1980s hits Kids In America and You Keep Me Hangin‚Äô On, the 56-year-old said: ‚ÄúI‚Äôm really excited to be announcing a new tour. I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôve toured the UK for over 30 years so I can‚Äôt wait to play this brand new show with my fantastic band. \n‚ÄúWe are going to be playing my biggest hits and some fabulous tracks from the new album which is coming out next spring. We can‚Äôt wait.‚Äù \nTickets go on general sale at 9am next Friday from www.ticketmaster.com. \nThe full line-up includes dates in Glasgow, Bath, Torquay, Bournemouth, Birmingham, Hastings, London and Salford over March and April 2018.",
