      "text": "Listen: Bank Of Ireland CEO Says The Tracker Scandal Is Being Taken Seriously. : 10/23/2017 - 16:25 \nThe CEO of Bank of Ireland says its taking the tracker mortgage scandal very seriously. \nFrancesca McDonagh is among several bank executives meeting with Finance Minister Pascal Donohoe today. \nEarlier Central Bank Governor Phillip Lane said he thinks the majority of customers caught up in the controversy will be compensated before Christmas. \nMs McDonagh spoke to reporters outside the Department of Finance this afternoon: \nOne of those affected by the tracker mortgage scandal is Cathriona Redmond. \nShe says its had a huge impact on her life: \nNEWSTALK144882.mp3, by Ciara Plunkett \nMeanwhile, the Finance Minister is due to brief the Cabinet on the situation later this evening. \nThe Taoiseach Leo Varadkar says the Government wants to see action from the banks - and if that doesn't happen the government will act: \nNEWSTALK1457536.mp3, by Ciara Plunkett \nImage: Francesca McDonagh, the incoming Bank of Ireland chief executive, arriving at the Department of Finance after being called to the Department of Finance over the tracker mortgage issues. Photo Leah Farrell/ RollingNews.ie",
