      "title": "Boundary changes slammed as 'bizarre'",
      "country": "GB",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T06:39:47Z",
      "url": "http://www.dumbartonreporter.co.uk/news/balloch_and_jamestown/15614112.Boundary_changes_slammed_as___39_bizarre__39_/",
      "host": "dumbartonreporter.co.uk",
      "text": "The MP for Dunbartonshire has branded as \"bizarre\" moves to include part of Bearsden in the constituency. \nMartin Docherty-Hughes says he fears the Boundary Commission proposal ignores the needs of local communities. \nThe commission is redrawing constituencies in an effort to cut the number of MPs from 650 to 600, with Scots MPs dropping from 59 to 53. \nBut the proposals have prompted a chorus of opposition across the country. \nThe Boundary Commission has proposed renaming the local constituency as Dunbartonshire West, in contrast to the council name. \nMr Docherty-Hughes said: ‚ÄúWhilst I welcome the Boundary Commission‚Äôs intention to retain all of the West Dunbartonshire Council area within a single constituency, its proposals to artificially attach part of Bearsden to the new Dunbartonshire West seat will seem bizarre to local residents. \n\"Dividing Bearsden between two constituencies is unnecessary and would not be in the best interests of effective local representation. \n‚ÄúIt‚Äôs clear that the needs of local communities are being ignored as the Tories seek to reduce the number of Scottish MPs at Westminster. \nHe added: \"Fiddling with constituency boundaries seems a misguided priority for the UK government as it struggles with Brexit, and in any case there is now no majority support in the House of Commons for these proposals.\" \nMr Hughes Docherty called on Theresa May to scrap the plans without delay \"to avoid any further waste of taxpayers‚Äô money\".",
