      "title": "Merkel ally warns EU intervention in Catalonia could create separatist DOMINO EFFECT",
      "country": "GB",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T10:12:59Z",
      "url": "http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/870401/Catalonia-European-Union-Italy-Lombardy-Veneto-Brexit-Angela-Merkel-CDU-David-McAllister",
      "host": "express.co.uk",
      "text": "Merkel ally warns EU intervention in Catalonia could create separatist DOMINO EFFECT Merkel ally warns EU intervention in Catalonia could create separatist DOMINO EFFECT THE CHAIR of the European Parliament‚Äôs foreign affairs committee warned that Brussels intervening in Catalonia could spark a wave of similar requests from across the continent. PUBLISHED: 10:33, Tue, Oct 24, 2017 | UPDATED: 11:15, Tue, Oct 24, 2017 \nDavid McAllister, an MEP from Angela Merkel‚Äôs CDU party, told France 24 that the issue was an internal one for Spain. \nBrussels has not intervened in the dispute between Barcelona and Madrid despite a brutal police crack down on an illegal independence referendum and the subsequent suspension of autonomy in Catalonia . \nMr McAllister said: ‚ÄúWell in the moment Catalonia is a case of its own. We had the question of possible Scottish independence in 2014, but I don't see other separatist movements going that far, either provincial government in Catalonia.‚Äù \n‚ÄúBut another argument against the involvement of the EU , or the EU commission is that here, of course, this could be a precedent for other cases. Getty/France 24 The CDU politician warned against intervening Catalonia. \n‚ÄúIf the EU starts negotiating here. Facilitating a dialogue, there could be similar calls coming from Northern Italy, from Flanders in Belgium, or from Corsica and France. \nMr McAllister said he understood some of the demands for autonomy across Europe but that this differed from outright separatist movements. \nHe said: ‚ÄúHonestly, I understand the wish of people having strong regions in Europe and I strongly believe in a Europe of nations, with strong regions.‚Äù \n‚ÄúFor instance, Germany, being a country with sixteen bundeslander, but strong regions are something different from having separatist movements. \n‚ÄúI don't believe that Europe successful if we fall into a dozen of new states.‚Äù \nItaly has been the latest European country to face a surge of support for separatist movements. The regions of Lombardy and Veneto voted for increased autonomy over the weekend. A number of other regions have separatist movements often based around linguistic or ethnic identity. \nMr McAllister is a powerful figure in EU circles and has been referred to as 'Merkel's man in Brussels' due to his close relationship with the German chancellor. \nThe German politician turned his fire on Brexit , which he says he ‚Äòdeeply regretted‚Äô as British people would suffer due to the negative consequences of leaving the bloc. Catalan referendum: Brutality of Catalonia's referendum vote Tue, October 3, 2017",
