      "title": "Leicester City v Leeds United: Christiansen won‚Äôt be taking managerless Foxes lightly",
      "country": "GB",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T01:56:12Z",
      "url": "http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leicester-city-v-leeds-united-christiansen-won-t-be-taking-managerless-foxes-lightly-1-8819626",
      "host": "yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk",
      "text": "Have your say \nThomas Christiansen has ordered his players to ignore Leicester City‚Äôs poor form and forget the idea that the Premier League club might be there for the taking when Leeds United bid to reach the Carabao Cup quarter-finals tomorrow. \nLeeds will be hosted by the former Premier League champions a week after Leicester reacted to a weak start to the season by sacking manager Craig Shakespeare. Leeds United head coach Thomas Christiansen. \nCity are under the caretaker control of assistant and former Oxford United boss Michael Appleton but a 2-1 win at Swansea City in Appleton‚Äôs first game in charge on Saturday lifted the club out of the top flight‚Äôs relegation places. \nLeicester have yet to decide on a permanent replacement for Shakespeare, who only replaced title winner Claudio Ranieri on a full-time basis in June, but United head coach Christiansen warned that this evening could be ‚Äúthe most dangerous time‚Äù to face a club who have experienced their share of turmoil since dramatically winning the Premier League in 2016. \nLeeds are attempting to scalp a top-flight side for the second time in the Carabao Cup having reached the last 16 by beating Burnley on penalties in the third round. \n‚ÄúLeicester had a good win this weekend, a win that can give them confidence back,‚Äù Christiansen said. Luke Ayling and Leeds United celebrate after beating Burnley on penalties in the third round of the Carabao Cup. \n‚ÄúYou never know when‚Äôs a good time (to play another club). When a team are hurt and they‚Äôre suffering down the table, that‚Äôs probably when it‚Äôs most dangerous to face them. You never know when is the right moment. \n‚ÄúWe faced Burnley when they were seventh in the league, playing well and getting important points and we managed to qualify for the next round. Anything can happen.‚Äù \nLeeds are looking for a second quarter-final appearance in two years having made the last eight of the League Cup under Garry Monk last season. United eventually suffered a narrow defeat to Jurgen Klopp‚Äôs Liverpool at Anfield. \nAsked about the lure of moving closer to the latter stages and a possible future appearance at Wembley, Christiansen said: ‚ÄúThose are big words but I will try to win all of our games and I‚Äôll try to pass as many rounds as possible ‚Äì trying to do it in the best way for the team. \n‚ÄúWe also have to face the reality that we‚Äôve faced one Premier League team, we‚Äôre going to face another one and, if we have the luck to pass to the next round, we‚Äôll face another, perhaps a very strong Premier League team. \n‚ÄúWe just have to enjoy the moment and the game in front of us.‚Äù \nChristiansen‚Äôs squad stabilised their own league form after three successive defeats with an impressive 3-0 win at Bristol City on Saturday, the first of three matches in seven days. \nUnited, who are fourth in the Championship, contest a Yorkshire derby against third-placed Sheffield United on Friday but Christiansen denied that he would prioritise that fixture over the trip to Leicester, saying: ‚ÄúBoth are important. More than looking at both games, I will look at the players I have.‚Äù \nThe Leeds boss, however, was pleased with a result at Ashton Gate which repaired damaged confidence at Elland Road following a sudden drop in the from which took the club to the top of the Championship last month. \n‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt lose (confidence) so fast and we don‚Äôt get it back so fast,‚Äù Christiansen said, ‚Äúbut it‚Äôs the beginning of us recovering that confidence. It comes when the players see they do things right but I see and I believe that all the players are giving their best.‚Äù Video - Leeds United: Foxes cup tie gives Jansson chance to push for recall - Christiansen Leeds United team news: Grieving Dallas to miss Leicester City trip Sign in",
