      "text": "Home / News / Cristiano Ronaldo Wins FIFA Men‚Äôs Player Of 2016-17 Cristiano Ronaldo Wins FIFA Men‚Äôs Player Of 2016-17 Tweet Updated: October 24, 2017 \nThe Real Madrid star has won the award for the second year in a row after leading the Blancos to a Liga and Champions League double. \nHe scored twice in a 4-1 win over Juventus in the continental final at Cardiff‚Äôs Millennium Stadium on June 3. \nRonaldo takes home the award for the second year in a row, as he managed to defeat competition from fellow finalists Neymar and Lionel Messi at the awards ceremony in London. \nReal boss Zinedine Zidane took the corresponding manager of the year award, with the Spanish giants providing five players in the FIFA team of the year. \nRonaldo won the inaugural Best FIFA men‚Äôs player of the year award last year following the end of a six-year merger between the FIFA honour and the Ballon D‚ÄôOr. \nRonaldo netted 25 times in La Liga last term and added 12 goals in the Champions League to round off another sensational goalscoring season. \nMessi, meanwhile, scored an incredible 54 goals in 52 appearances in all competitions last term, but only managed to get his hands on the Copa del Rey with Barca ‚Äì and it was ultimately Madrid‚Äôs title wins that assured victory for their star forward. \n‚ÄúThank you, a lot, to the guys who voted for me. I must also mention Leo and Neymar, for being here,‚Äù Ronaldo said after recieving the prize. \n‚ÄúReal Madrid ‚Äì the coach, the supporters and the president ‚Äì they support all of the year so I say thank you to them. \n‚ÄúI‚Äôm really glad to win consecutive awards. This is a great moment for me. Thank you to all the fans around the world for the support. I appreciate that, thank you very much. \n‚ÄúIt‚Äôs great to be here with these great players and I am so happy guys, thanks you so much.‚Äù \nThe Best FIFA Men‚Äôs Player nod wasn‚Äôt the only honour Ronaldo picked up on the evening, as he was also named to the FIFPro World 11 for the 11th year in a row . \nElsewhere on the night, Arsenal striker Olivier Giroud won the FIFA Puskas Award for the best goal of 2016-17, Real Madrid boss Zinedine Zidane took home the Men‚Äôs Coach of the Year prize, and Juventus veteran Gianluigi Buffon was named the Best FIFA Goalkeeper Don't be selfish...",
