      "host": "dailystar.co.uk",
      "text": "Getty Michy Batshuayi celebrates putting himself firmly back in the Chelsea fold \nThe Blues forward was snubbed by boss Antonio Conte when fellow attacker Alvaro Morata came off injured against Manchester City. \nMidfielder Willian was brought on in his place, sparking reports Batshuayi's time at Stamford Bridge may be over before it even really began. \nHowever, when given his chance from the bench against Watford on Saturday, the 24-year-old seized the opportunity, scoring twice and winning the game for Chelsea. \nAnd club captain Gary Cahill believes the Belgian has proved he can be part of Chelsea's success this season. \n\"I‚Äôm sure he has things to improve but as a player that‚Äôs exactly how you respond,\" he told Chelsea's official website. Chelsea‚Äôs likely line-up to face Everton at home in Carabao Cup CHELSEA host Everton in the Carabao Cup on Wednesday night, but who will start the game? 1 / 13 Chelsea (Odds: 2/5 to win, 18/5 to draw, 15/2 to lose) ‚ÄúHe scored two goals and arguably won us the game‚Äù Gary Cahill on Michy Batshuayi \n\"He‚Äôs come on and changed the game for us. \n\"He scored two goals and arguably won us the game. \n\"I‚Äôm very pleased for him and I‚Äôm sure the manager and all the coaches are pleased for him. \nGetty Michy Batshuayi is greeted by Antonio Conte after his two goals gave Chelsea three points Related videos",
