      "text": "Get daily   Thank you for subscribing!   \nNeymar faced the awkward moment of reuniting with Lionel Messi in the public eye at the Best FIFA Best Awards. \nNeither of the South American stars claimed the top prize as Cristiano Ronaldo scooped the men's player of the year. \nBut the PSG forward discussed chatting with his former team-mate after spending four seasons together. \n\"I spoke to Bartomeu in a normal fashion,\" Neymar revealed to Radio Marca. \"[Messi and I] didn't speak about football, only other things. \n\"He is my friend and wherever we are, we will be together.\" \nThe animosity between Neymar and Barcelona president Josep Maria Bartomeu exists after the Brazilian's contract was bought out for almost ¬£200m. \nBartomeu's bitterness stems from his belief Neymar's departure was fuelled by greed and money. Neymar and Messi played together for four seasons (Image: Getty Images Europe) Lionel Messi and wife Antonella Roccuzzo arrive (Image: Getty Images Europe) \nThe votes from the manager and captain of each national team nominates were revealed. A media representative from each country was given the same opportunity. \nArgentina captain Messi voted for Luis Suarez (first), Andres Iniesta (second) and Neymar (third). The shortlist for the top men's player of the year was Lionel Messi, Cristiano Ronaldo and Neymar (Image: Getty Images Europe) \nEngland captain Jordan Henderson voted for Ronaldo then Messi and then former team-mate Suarez. Three Lions manager Gareth Southgate, meanwhile, opted for Ronaldo, Modric and Toni Kroos. \nWales captain Ashley Williams did not take part in the vote. His manager Chris Coleman did, however. He picked Ramos, Modric and Harry Kane. \nTottenham striker Kane also picked up nominations from British Virgin Islands captain Troy Ceasar Kavon, France skipper Hugo Lloris, Motserrat's Anthony Griffith and Dio Godet of the Bahamas. \nOther Premier League players to pick up nominations include Alexis Sanchez, N'Golo Kante, Eden Hazard and Zlatan Ibrahimovic. Harry Kane picked up a few votes (Image: Getty Images Europe) \nScotland manager Gordon Strachan Voted for Modric, Kante and Messi while captain Scott Brown went for Ronaldo, Messi and Neymar. \nNorthern Ireland skipper Steven Davis selected Rnaldo, Messi and Gianluigi Buffon while his international manager Michael O'Neill chose Ronaldo, Hazard and Kante. \nSouth of the border, Republic of Ireland manager Martin O'Neill voted for Ronaldo, Messi and Hazard. Seamus Coleman selected Ronaldo, Messi and Juventus forward Paulo Dybala. \nGermany captain Manuel Neuer voted for Kroos, Robert Lewandowski and Arturo Vidal. World Cup winning manager Joachim Low voted for Kroos, Neuer and Neymar. The full list of votes: (Image: FIFA)",
