      "url": "http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/how-ronald-koemans-everton-sacking-13802519",
      "host": "liverpoolecho.co.uk",
      "text": "How Ronald Koeman's Everton sacking unfolded during a Manic Monday at Goodison Park The Blues are looking for a new boss, with David Unsworth and John Ebbrell in temporary charge   Everton FC   Could   \nIn the end it turned into a Manic Monday at Goodison Park. \nThe morning papers had lamented another hopeless Everton showing, while across social media Blues fans had their say. Plenty wanted a change. \nStill, the feeling generally was that it was unlikely ‚Äì for now at least. \nAnd then at 1.30pm, came the four-line statement that would change everything. \n‚ÄúEverton Football Club can confirm that Ronald Koeman has left the club,‚Äù it read. \n‚ÄúChairman Bill Kenwright, the board of directors and major shareholder Farhad Moshiri would all like to express their gratitude to Ronald for the service he has given to the club over the past 16 months and for guiding the club to seventh place in last season‚Äôs Premier League campaign.‚Äù \nHe'd gone. Koeman - in his own words \nEarlier in the day Dutch journalist, and Koeman confidante, Marcel van der Kraan had told Sky Sports News that Koeman still felt he had the backing of both Kenwright and Moshiri; he didn't, he said, feel ‚Äúfinished‚Äù. \nHis faith was swiftly proven misplaced. He leaves Everton in the bottom three of the Premier League, having overseen their worst start to a season in a dozen years. They're struggling for goals at one end, and leaking them alarmingly at the other. \nHe will be followed out of the door by his brother Erwin, his first-team coach, as well as fitness coach Jan Kluitenberg and goalkeeping coach Patrick Lodewijks. \nDavid Unsworth and John Ebbrell, Everton's U23s coaches, will take charge of the first-team as they prepare for Wednesday's Carabao Cup trip to Chelsea. Unsworth could be given longer than his last interim spell, which was just one game, as the Blues consider their options in terms of a long-term successor. Read More",
