      "text": "Click to followES Sport Swansea vs Manchester United: EFL Cup prediction, team line-ups and where to watch on TV and online Popular Videos \nJose Mourinho will be hoping to get back to winning ways as Manchester United continue their EFL Cup defence against Swansea City . \nHolders United beat Burton Albion 4-1 last month to ease into the last-16 of the competition, but Mourinho must rally his troops after a dispiriting Premier League defeat at Huddersfield Town last Saturday. \nTher Red Devils were well below par as they lost their unbeaten League record, but Mourinho will likely ring the changes as he looks to defend one of the two trophies he won in his first year in charge at Old Trafford. \nScroll down for Standard Sport's comprehensive preview... Start time \nSwansea host Manchester United at Liberty Stadium with kick-off scheduled for 7.45pm on Tuesday, October 24. TV and live online coverage \nThe match will be televised live in the UK on Sky Sports' Football and Main Event channels, with coverage starting from 7:30pm. Alternatively, you can follow all the team news and goals with Standard Sport‚Äôs live scoreboard blog. Live Updates",
