      "host": "hitc.com",
      "text": "Newcastle United midfielder Mikel Merino not fazed by takeover talk at St. James' Park.\n\nMikel Merino has told the Chronicle that he is not too concerned about the off field activity at Newcastle United .\nNewcastle are currently up for sale, and it appears that Amanda Staveley is edging closer to agreeing a deal with Mike Ashley to buy the club.\nNewcastle are expected to have more money to spend if they are taken over by Staveley, and that should enable them to compete for honours in the Premier League .\n\nBut Merino insists that he is not letting the excitement of the potential takeover impact on his performances.\n‚ÄúPersonally I don‚Äôt think much about the takeover, I don‚Äôt know what my team-mates think,‚Äù the Spanish midfielder said.\n‚ÄúWe just have to focus on football because other things can distract you. We can‚Äôt worry about other things.‚Äù\nMerino joined Newcastle during the summer transfer window, and he has immediately impressed at St. James‚Äô Park.\n\nThe 21-year-old‚Äôs loan move from Borussia Dortmund has already been made permanent, with Newcastle acting quickly to snap up the midfielder.\nMerino scored Newcastle‚Äôs winner in their most recent fixture, as Rafael Benitez‚Äôs side overcame the challenge of Crystal Palace.\nNewcastle have made an impressive start to their campaign, and currently sit in seventh place in the Premier League table.\n\nShow Comments",
