      "text": "24.10.2017, 12:46 Piston chief vehemently denies representing NDFP in row with columnist George San Mateo, Piston president, discusses the jeepney modernization program on Tuesday, Oct. 24, 2017, at the Pandesal Forum in Quezon City. (Photo by NOY MOSCOSO / INQURIER.net) \nGeorge San Mateo, president of the Pinagkaisang Samahan ng mga Tsuper at Opereytor Nationwide (Piston), vehemently denied being a representative of the National Democratic Front of the Philippines (NDFP) on Tuesday, during a heated exchange with a newspaper columnist Herman ‚ÄúMentong‚Äù Tiu Laurel. \nThe debate started at the Pandesal Forum, a weekly event at the Kamuning Bakery Caf√© in Quezon City, when Laurel asked San Mateo if Piston was a political organization backed by progressive and left-leaning groups. \n‚ÄúNakakalungkot nga si Presidente [Rodrigo Duterte],‚Äù San Mateo told Laurel. ‚ÄúYung sinasabi niyang political group dahil sumuporta yung KMU [Kilusang Mayo Uno], eh nakipag-dialogue din naman siya dyan eh.‚Äù \nSan Mateo added, however, that he would still be willing to talk with the President to settle issues on the public utility vehicles (PUV) modernization program. \nBut Herman insisted on asking if San Mateo if he was representing NDFP. \n‚ÄúAno kinalaman nun? Namulitika siya eh ang isyu ay modernization?‚Äù San Mateo asked Herman. \n‚ÄúI‚Äôm not a representative of the NDF here,‚Äù he added. ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not a representative of the CPP [Communist Party of the Philippines], nor the KMU nor Bayan. I‚Äôm representing Piston. Don‚Äôt say na kami ay nagde-destabilize. You‚Äôre way out of line.‚Äù \nSan Mateo even admitted voting for Duterte in the May 2016 elections as president because of his promises that he would revive the steel industry in the country, a promise that, he said, was later ‚Äúbroken.‚Äù \n‚ÄúKung makapagtayo tayo ng steel industry marami na tayo magagawa nun,‚Äù he said. ‚ÄúMakakagawa tayo ng sasakyan, yung agrikultura mamo-modernize natin. Kaya lang after a year wala na tayong narinig tungkol sa pangako nya.‚Äù \nIn a speech last week, Duterte tagged Piston, KMU and Karapatan as legal fronts of the CPP-New People‚Äôs Army after the militant groups supported Piston‚Äôs nationwide transport strike on Oct. 16 to 17. /atm Subscribe to INQUIRER PLUS to get access to The Philippine Daily Inquirer & other 70+ titles, share up to 5 gadgets, listen to the news, download as early as 4am & share articles on social media. Call 896 6000.",
